SAQAMAW, (plural Saqamaq): A "Chief" of a local [[Mi'kmaq]] [[First Nation]] Community in [[Quebec]], [[Canada]], [[Maine]], [[United States]], [[Newfoundland]], [[New Brunswick]] or [[Nova Scotia]].

Translated into [[English language|English]], it can mean: 
* gentleman 
* chief 
* man of high rank 
* big shot 

